    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an energy bar chart with two bars labeled K and U. The vertical axis is labeled Energy, and 0 is indicated, with grid lines above and below 0. Bar K is positive 3 units. Bar U is negative 4 units.\" src=\"/images/062b8c041bd60e04fd365c3eae55983c.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A satellite is in an elliptical orbit around Earth. The energy bar chart represents the relative kinetic energy <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"K\"><math alttext=\"K\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>K</mi></math></span></span> of the satellite and the gravitational potential energy <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U\"><math alttext=\"U\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>U</mi></math></span></span> of the satellite-Earth system when the satellite is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> from the center of Earth. At a later time, the satellite is a distance <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">greater than</span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> from the center of Earth. Which of the following bar graphs could represent the values of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"K\"><math alttext=\"K\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>K</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"U\"><math alttext=\"U\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>U</mi></math></span></span> at this later time?</p>\n",
